    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "MISEA/TAC TO ALL THE WORLD\nPACIFIC\nNORTHW\nE\nNORTHWEST",
      "Seattle-Tacoma\nInternational Airport is located\nabout half-way between the two cities and serv-\ning them both. A Northwest Orient Airlines 720B\nFan-Jet (Boeing) is being loaded here, with pas-\nsengers boarding the plane through the moveable\nramp. In back looms snow-covered Mount Rainier\nin its majestic grandeur.\nC14977— Color Photo by Max R. Jensen\nMikel\nRoberta\nBERKELEY 2, CALIF\nPublished by C. P. Johnston Company, Seattle, Washington\n2015.166.2311\n(AVIBTON)\n35"
    ],
